Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.58,0:00:03.65,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}As bright as a spark,\Nwith a sharp and precise wit.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.65,0:00:05.30,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Once he gets started, you can't stop him!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.30,0:00:07.13,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Stay right there for a sudden reversal of circumstances!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.13,0:00:08.98,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Today's episode has the smallest cast ever!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.98,0:00:10.82,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}He sees the single truth for what it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.82,0:00:12.74,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}and looks like a kid but has the mind of an adult!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.74,0:00:15.05,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}His name? Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.46,0:01:55.33,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}A car rigged with an explosive blew up at the home of the parents
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.33,0:01:59.27,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}of Megumi Sakihara-{\i1}san{\i0}, a person who the old guy used to tutor in his school days.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.35,0:02:04.57,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}The victim who passed away in the incident was Megumi-{\i1}san{\i0}'s younger sister Hiromi-{\i1}san{\i0},
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.57,0:02:06.88,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}who was backing the car out of the garage for Megumi-{\i1}san{\i0},
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.88,0:02:09.82,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}because she was supposedly not good at it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.33,0:02:15.18,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}The suspect was a man named Hiromasa Takahashi.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.18,0:02:19.45,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}He agreed to carry out an exchange murder with Megumi-{\i1}san{\i0}'s husband Kazuo Sakihara,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.45,0:02:24.75,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}but he inadvertently kills Hiromi-{\i1}san{\i0} instead of Megumi-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.24,0:02:30.12,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Both men confessed to their crime,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.12,0:02:32.29,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}and it looked like the case was solved. But...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.24,0:02:39.06,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}She backed out of a parking space that narrow...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.17,0:02:47.22,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}This case isn't solved yet!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.92,0:02:57.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}! What's gotten into you?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.15,0:02:58.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, did something happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.57,0:03:01.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, it's nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.36,0:03:05.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I think Megumi-{\i1}san{\i0} came here to buy us some cake or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.14,0:03:07.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's hurry and go to Megumi-{\i1}san{\i0}'s house!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.77,0:03:11.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Geez. What's with that kid anyway?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.35,0:03:15.16,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}It's too early to tell the old man about this.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.16,0:03:17.56,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}I've got to get more solid proof.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.80,0:03:25.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I, uh... I just don't know what to say...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.62,0:03:31.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you very much. I'm fine, so please don't worry about me.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.43,0:03:32.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I-I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.74,0:03:36.78,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Please have some tea before it gets cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.78,0:03:39.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.02,0:03:40.22,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll have some too.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.22,0:03:42.22,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,How about some cake, Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.92,0:03:45.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sure!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.27,0:03:48.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,May I go to the restroom first?{lit. "before that, toilet where?"}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.21,0:04:01.16,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Over there...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.34,0:04:28.50,Flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Sakihara had a phone exclusively for himself upstairs
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.50,0:04:30.79,Flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}and took all his calls with that phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.87,0:04:56.88,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.27,0:05:02.38,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}That's the remains of masking tape that was peeled off!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.75,0:05:05.66,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Just as I thought...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.67,0:05:10.06,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}So, "it" was set up there after all...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.69,0:05:19.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll bet you're relieved that Megumi-{\i1}san{\i0} looked way better than you expected, right, Dad?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.87,0:05:23.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. I think she'll be fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.03,0:05:27.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I've got somewhere to go when we get to Beika Station,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.36,0:05:28.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,so you can both leave me and go home.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.49,0:05:31.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,All right, but remember, don't be too late.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.29,0:05:55.36,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}There's a window...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.89,0:05:59.05,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}I see... If it's from that window...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.49,0:06:04.49,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Just as I thought...!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.87,0:06:12.73,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Okay! I've got the overall picture! Now all I need is proof!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.10,0:06:17.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm back!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.12,0:06:23.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Uncle...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.86,0:06:28.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Something bothers me about the case.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.43,0:06:29.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.64,0:06:31.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Because, remember Megumi-{\i1}san{\i0} backed her car
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.76,0:06:35.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,out of the narrow parking space at the supermarket today, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.60,0:06:37.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then why did she have her younger sister back her car out for her
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.38,0:06:39.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,when the incident happened...?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.30,0:06:47.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, on the wall near the telephone of the upstairs study of Megumi-{\i1}san{\i0}'s house,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.27,0:06:49.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,it looked like masking tape was peeled off.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.58,0:06:51.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That means that something was stuck on there, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.77,0:06:53.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Masking tape?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.17,0:07:02.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you know that there was a window way inside the garage
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.06,0:07:04.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,where the incident occurred, Uncle?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.46,0:07:06.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It seems that the window cracked from the impact of the explosion
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.94,0:07:09.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and a wooden board was placed over it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.13,0:07:10.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But with a window like that over there,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.61,0:07:13.19,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,it's good because you can get a good view of the car from inside the house.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.27,0:07:16.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you trying to get at?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.87,0:07:22.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you insinuating that Megumi-{\i1}kun{\i0} has something to do with this case?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.51,0:07:26.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know. But...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.62,0:07:28.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be ridiculous!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.99,0:07:34.79,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I know her best because she used to be my student!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.76,0:07:39.47,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You knew her as a high school student, right, Uncle?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.33,0:07:46.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Megumi-{\i1}san{\i0} could've changed after growing up.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.87,0:07:47.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you dare get cheeky with me!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.84,0:07:53.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She hasn't changed a bit! She's the way she always used to be!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.89,0:07:56.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You want to believe that, don't you, Uncle?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.56,0:07:57.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.45,0:08:00.79,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But actually, she's already...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.00,0:08:04.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up and go on upstairs!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.29,0:08:08.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll go take a bath.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.75,0:08:19.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Geez! How dare that brat talk to me like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.06,0:08:24.43,Flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}A secret window?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.21,0:08:30.11,Flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Yes, Hiromi and I call it that.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.38,0:08:30.11,Character Card,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}{\fad(500,0)}Megumi During High School
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.01,0:08:34.63,Flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}It seems that Dad actually wanted to use this as a door, though...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.59,0:08:41.43,Flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}When I was little and getting into things in the garage,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.43,0:08:44.11,Flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}I would always be scolded from here...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.01,0:08:55.96,Character Card,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Metropolitan Police Department
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.47,0:08:55.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The record of the testimonies of Sakihara and Takahashi?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.96,0:09:00.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. I'd like to take a quick look, and review the results.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.43,0:09:04.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Did anything new come up in later investigations?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.09,0:09:08.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Now that you mention it, one of Hiromi-{\i1}san{\i0}'s friends told me
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.16,0:09:12.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,that when Hiromi-{\i1}san{\i0} was younger, she took two boyfriends away from Megumi-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.94,0:09:20.38,Flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Well, I guess you could say that she was very carefree...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.75,0:09:24.17,Flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}It seems that Hiromi-{\i1}san{\i0} was only fooling around for the fun of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.17,0:09:28.18,Flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}But it seems that when Megumi-{\i1}san{\i0} decided to marry Sakihara,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.18,0:09:30.97,Flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}although jokingly, she told her that if she did it again,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.97,0:09:33.41,Flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}she would make her pay for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.42,0:09:45.05,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Most likely, the old guy will find some sort of circumstantial evidence in his investigation.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.06,0:09:49.55,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}But when it comes to concrete evidence...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.83,0:10:05.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I've got it! Maybe...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.61,0:10:09.74,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Inspector, about what I asked you over the phone a while ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.74,0:10:12.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. I confirmed with Takahashi,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.58,0:10:16.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but the only time he saw her face was at that supermarket.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.69,0:10:21.92,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}That's the first and last time he ever appeared before Megumi-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.92,0:10:25.19,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And, how was Takahashi dressed at that time?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.09,0:10:27.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He was wearing a jacket and sunglasses.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.80,0:10:29.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Just as I thought!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.85,0:10:33.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Mouri-{\i1}kun{\i0}, what are you up to anyway?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.70,0:10:37.23,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Thank you very much, Inspector! Goodbye!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.23,0:10:39.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,H-Hey! Mouri-{\i1}kun{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.39,0:10:44.61,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Okay! Now I've got the proof!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.37,0:11:26.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? What do you mean? Hey, Dad?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.22,0:11:29.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He hung up.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.32,0:11:32.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What's the matter, Ran-{\i1}neechan{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.16,0:11:36.78,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Dad's in Akihabara, and says he's about to go to Megumi-{\i1}san{\i0}'s house.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.45,0:11:41.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He said he's "the only one who can persuade her"...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.03,0:11:42.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder what he means?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.40,0:11:46.47,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ran-{\i1}neechan{\i0}, let's go to Megumi-{\i1}san{\i0}'s house too!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.88,0:11:49.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Geez!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.82,0:11:52.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Why'd you guys have to come too?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.56,0:11:56.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry. I was really concerned about your call.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.31,0:12:04.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry to keep you waiting.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.48,0:12:06.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.20,0:12:11.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So what did you want to talk to me about?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.40,0:12:17.47,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Megumi-{\i1}kun{\i0}. I came here today to advise you to turn yourself in.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.63,0:12:20.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.21,0:12:33.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,After finding out that your husband and your younger sister were having an affair,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.82,0:12:40.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,as an exchange murder was being planned between your husband and Takahashi,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.39,0:12:42.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,you decided to use all this
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.59,0:12:45.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,to kill your younger sister that you have always hated,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.92,0:12:50.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and send your husband to jail on charges of murder, isn't that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.75,0:12:53.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Dad, what a thing to say!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.19,0:13:02.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Two months ago, you bought a wiretap and automatic recorder at a shop in Akihabara.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.62,0:13:05.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You asked the salesperson to give you the details on how to use the machines.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.20,0:13:12.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,These are the same modular-type wiretap and automatic recorder that you bought!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.67,0:13:15.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't want to do it,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.80,0:13:20.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but when I went to the restroom a while ago, I checked out the upstairs study.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.17,0:13:25.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You rigged a wiretap to your husband's study
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.63,0:13:29.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and bugged his conversations with Takahashi.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.04,0:13:32.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The remains of masking tape peeled off the wall is proof.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.80,0:13:38.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You were probably planning to listen to the conversation
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.67,0:13:40.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,between your husband and your younger sister at first, weren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.56,0:13:45.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But along the way, you found out something absolutely dreadful...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.29,0:13:51.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,that your husband had agreed to an exchange murder with a complete stranger
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.73,0:13:55.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and that he had already killed the wife of that man...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.36,0:14:00.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The time came when it was your turn to be killed by that man Takahashi.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.53,0:14:04.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You found out that he was planning to rig your car with an explosive,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.46,0:14:06.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but was undecided because if he does so in front of your house
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.16,0:14:10.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,your husband Kazuo, may turn up as a suspect to...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.48,0:14:12.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So you deliberately told your husband
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.48,0:14:16.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,you were driving over to your sister's place,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.44,0:14:20.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,because her car just happened to be at the shop for inspection,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.00,0:14:23.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and the garage was open.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.23,0:14:27.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Your husband then goes out to a pay phone
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.69,0:14:30.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and tells Takahashi everything you told him.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.81,0:14:33.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Although you didn't listen to their phone conversation,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.37,0:14:37.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,almost positive that Takahashi was going to carry out his murder plan,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.70,0:14:39.19,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,you went over to Hiromi's.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.03,0:14:44.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And after telling Hiromi that you were not good at backing cars,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.17,0:14:43.17,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Megumi's Parents' Home
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.15,0:14:47.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,you made her back the car out of the garage for you
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.12,0:14:51.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,As expected, your younger sister died.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.91,0:14:59.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But at that time, just one thing that you didn't expect happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.70,0:15:03.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I happened to come and see you!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.19,0:15:06.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You were surprised and...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.82,0:15:07.84,Flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Wait, {\i1}Sensei{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.43,0:15:09.53,Flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Good.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.19,0:15:12.29,Flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Alright, alright...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.90,0:15:13.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You wanted her to back out right away
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.03,0:15:17.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,because you didn't want me to see through your plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.82,0:15:26.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I did buy the wiretap, as you say.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.73,0:15:34.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I set it up behind the desk after suspecting my husband of having an affair.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.69,0:15:37.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But I thought it over that night and immediately threw it away.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.58,0:15:39.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So I didn't actually use it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.31,0:15:42.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you know that the person he was having an affair with was your younger sister?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.44,0:15:45.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I had no idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.07,0:15:59.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's presume—this is just a presumption, now—that I did act as you had deduced,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.40,0:16:01.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,what crime am I guilty of?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.11,0:16:10.19,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Takahashi is the one who rigged the explosive onto the car,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.19,0:16:12.19,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and the person who put him up to it is my husband.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.91,0:16:17.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,All I did, if anything, was make my younger sister get into a car
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.42,0:16:19.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,that may have been rigged with explosives.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.82,0:16:23.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not an accomplice in a crime, nor did I urge anyone to commit murder for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.46,0:16:26.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that right, {\i1}Sensei{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.64,0:16:33.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Just as expected of a student in the law department, and a lawyer's daughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.72,0:16:38.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Just as you say,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.66,0:16:40.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,if all you did was get your younger sister to ride the car,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.61,0:16:42.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,you wouldn't be found guilty of anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.98,0:16:43.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.76,0:16:44.47,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,However.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.59,0:16:49.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,in the case that you made your sister get in the car despite knowing
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.46,0:16:54.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,that an explosive was rigged to the car, or if there was a good chance you knew,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.98,0:16:56.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,you would be charged with homicide!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.58,0:17:02.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You mentioned back then...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.42,0:17:05.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,that you had to look for something, and went into the closet alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.02,0:17:08.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then you watched the garage from the window.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.67,0:17:12.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And, just as expected, Takahashi came into the garage
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.90,0:17:15.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,to set the explosive onto the car.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.99,0:17:21.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,After you confirmed all that, you asked your sister to back the car out.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.20,0:17:26.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, there was a very good chance that the explosive was
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.12,0:17:30.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,being rigged to the car, and you still made your sister drive it!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.11,0:17:34.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you have any proof that I was watching the garage through the closet?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.19,0:17:37.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If you do, please show it to me right now!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.35,0:17:38.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Right now!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.60,0:17:45.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You've got proof, Uncle.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.56,0:17:50.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Remember? The sketch of the man that Megumi-{\i1}san{\i0} said she saw,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.32,0:17:51.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,that was drawn by police officer Honjo.{where is the translator getting this name?}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.91,0:18:00.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Megumi-{\i1}san{\i0}, where did you say you saw his face?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.62,0:18:02.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A-At the supermarket near my house.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.38,0:18:06.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Strange. The officer mentioned that Takahashi
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.59,0:18:11.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,was wearing a jacket and sunglasses back then.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.92,0:18:15.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But why is the man in the sketch not wearing sunglasses?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.47,0:18:26.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Megumi-{\i1}san{\i0}, you didn't even notice Takahashi watching you at the supermarket, did you?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.49,0:18:33.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You found out only after you listened to Kazuo-{\i1}san{\i0}'s phone call that you tapped, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.32,0:18:36.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then where did she see his face?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.49,0:18:37.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,From the closet!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.93,0:18:42.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She saw him from the secret window of the closet.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.70,0:19:03.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Megumi-{\i1}kun{\i0}, you were watching Takahashi's face from the closet of your parents' house!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.62,0:19:08.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The face of Takahashi who was setting up the explosive!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.60,0:19:11.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,H-How can you be so sure?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.23,0:19:16.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That day, Takahashi didn't want anybody to notice him,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.99,0:19:20.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,so he was wearing sunglasses until he entered the garage.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.37,0:19:22.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course, he were his sunglasses when coming out too.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.41,0:19:28.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But there was just one time he had to take off his sunglasses!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.02,0:19:34.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It was when he was setting the explosive onto the car!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.08,0:19:41.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Because nobody would even dream of doing a dangerous job
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.15,0:19:46.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,like setting up an explosive onto a car while wearing sunglasses
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.63,0:19:53.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, this sketch of Takahashi without his sunglasses is proof that
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.38,0:19:58.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,you witnessed Takahashi rigging the explosive to the car in the garage!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.71,0:20:16.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Just as you say, I happened to hear them.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.02,0:20:21.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He was planning to kill me and use the insurance money that I was covered with,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.34,0:20:23.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,along with the inheritance money my parents left for me,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.86,0:20:26.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,to open a new boutique that Hiromi was to own...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.45,0:20:33.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, I remember the good old days...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.03,0:20:43.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I was really happy back then...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.16,0:20:49.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I kept hoping that I could go back to those good old days all this time...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.92,0:20:54.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.42,0:20:58.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,15 years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.59,0:21:02.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,there was something very important that I was supposed to have taught you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.86,0:21:08.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Something more important than studying.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.07,0:21:12.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But, maybe I can't really teach you much,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.97,0:21:16.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,since I'm separated from my wife and all now.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.92,0:21:17.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,True!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.10,0:21:22.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But it's not too late.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.20,0:21:25.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Repent for the crime that you have committed and study all over again.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.93,0:21:28.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This time, the study of life!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.10,0:21:32.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Will you watch over me... then again?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.15,0:21:35.47,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sure! By all means!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.64,0:23:24.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's good that the case was solved, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.72,0:23:28.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This case must've really come as a shock to Uncle...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.14,0:23:38.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, Mouri Detective Agency...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.41,0:23:40.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yoko-{\i1}chan{\i0}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.95,0:23:45.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A concert? Of course I'll go!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.36,0:23:48.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If for you, I'll go and cheer for you or tutor.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.45,0:23:50.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll do anything you wish! Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.37,0:23:53.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess we've got nothing to worry about.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.93,0:23:58.02,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Really! It takes the old guy no time at all to get back on his feet.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.47,0:24:03.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It bothers me! I met him somewhere,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.36,0:24:06.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but I can't remember where...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.07,0:24:09.47,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}An MO disc?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.80,0:24:12.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.54,0:24:15.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't remember buying this...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.65,0:24:19.27,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}The old man who disappeared! The man wearing sunglasses!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.70,0:24:24.01,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Something... Something smells fishy!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.01,0:24:30.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Next Conan:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.03,0:24:35.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Next Conan's Hint: Window glass
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.03,0:24:36.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Next time, a mysterious old man!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.07,0:24:38.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Geez, young people these days!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.04,0:24:39.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Is he the mysterious old man?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.10,0:24:40.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}No idea.
